flavorText: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.
It lives in warm seas. It is said that a couple finding this Pokémon will be blessed with eternal love.
Rather than rely on force, they master moves that utilize the centrifugal force of spinning concrete.
It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene-splicing and DNA-engineering experiments.
This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.
Standing on its hind legs freed its forelegs and made it smarter. It is very forgetful, however.
It emits light from its tail to communicate. It loves the sweet aroma given off by Illumise.
The gear with the red core is rotated at high speed for a rapid energy charge.
Pokémon living in the forest eat the delicious caps on Morelull's head. The caps regrow overnight.
Its hearing is so acute it can hear a pin drop over half a mile away. It lives on quiet mountains.
It hefts a GRAVELER repeatedly to strengthen its entire body. It uses every type of martial arts.
This Pokémon lived in primeval jungles. Few enemies would have been willing to square off against its heavily armored face, so it's thought.
The heads on their arms do not have brains. They use all three heads to consume and destroy everything.
It's said that not even pro wrestlers can take down a Machop.
If it smells something enticing, it dashes off headlong to find the source of the aroma.
Durant dig nests in mountains. They build their complicated, interconnected tunnels into mazes.
When the sun goes down, it becomes active. It runs around town on a chase for good food for the boss of its nest—Raticate.
Psychic power allows these Pokémon to fly. Some say they were the guardians of an ancient city. Others say they were the guardians' emissaries.
It expresses its feelings by smacking its scales. Metallic sounds echo through the tall mountains where Jangmo-o lives.
It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.
It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body and guide them home.
It rolls across ice floes to reach shore because its body is poorly shaped for swimming.
They fight at Bisharp's command. They cling to their prey and inflict damage by sinking their blades into it.
The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.
These Pokémon evolve by wearing the shell covering of a Shelmet. The steel armor protects their whole body.
It forms a group of Rattata, which it assumes command of. Each group has its own territory, and disputes over food happen often.
If it bonds with a person, it will gently envelop the friend with its soft wings, then hum.
With four linked brains, it's more intelligent than a supercomputer, and it uses calculations to analyze foes.
Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe Mew to be the ancestor of Pokémon.
It drifts on winds. It is said that when HOPPIP gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.
Its round body is stuffed with souls and expands each time it leads someone away.
Stores up electricity in its body, then suddenly releases it to surprise and shock everyone.
It leaps at its prey with a courageous shout. Its scaly punches tear its opponents to shreds.
This extremely wise Pokémon excels at rescuing people stranded at sea or in the mountains.
It captivates foes with its huge, round eyes, then lulls them to sleep by singing a soothing melody.
It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.
It may drop out of the sky suddenly. If attacked by a Spearow, it violently shakes its leaves.
Each of its hands contains different toxins, but both hands can jab with near-fatal power.
It boasts superb physical strength. Those who wish to become Pangoro's Trainer have no choice but to converse with their fists.
Bisharp pursues prey in the company of a large group of Pawniard. Then Bisharp finishes off the prey.
It sends a soothing aura from its ribbonlike feelers to calm fights.
It converses with others by using magnetic pulses. In a swarm, they move in perfect unison.
If its body is torn, it can grow back if the red core remains. The core flashes at midnight.
It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.
It can telepathically communicate with people. It changes its appearance using its down that refracts light.
It toughens its body by slamming into thick trees. Many snapped trees can be found near its nest.
When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it's decorated with cream.
Uses anti-gravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses attacks like Thunder Wave.
It has a timid nature. If it is startled, the flames on its back burn more vigorously.
Research continues on this Pokémon, which could be the power source of a unique motor.
Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.
It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.
This legendary Pokémon battled against humans to protect Pokémon. Its personality is calm and composed.
Burrows to suck tree roots. The mushrooms on its back grow by drawing nutrients from the bug host.
It takes pride in the speed at which it can use moves. What it loses in power, it makes up for in quantity.
From the slight twitches of its bamboo leaf, it deduces its opponent's movements. It's eager to tussle but kindhearted toward its companions.
Because the long hair all over its body obscures its sight, it just keeps charging repeatedly.
The units at its sides generate electromagnetic waves that keep it airborne. It feeds on electricity.
If they scent the faintest trace of blood, they rush to attack en masse. When alone, they're rather cowardly.
If you build sand mounds when you're playing, destroy them before you go home, or they may get possessed and become Sandygast.
Despite the beauty of its lilting voice, it's merciless to intruders that enter its territory.
This Pokémon wanders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.
Adores round objects. It wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.
It eats dreams and releases mist. The mist is pink when it's eating a good dream, and black when it's eating a nightmare.
A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.
Each follows its Trainer's orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.
A Grimer, which had been brought in to solve a problem with garbage, developed over time into this form.
It understands human speech and is highly intelligent. It is a tender Pokémon that dislikes fighting.
It is known to drift on winds if it is bloated to bursting with stored electricity.
There's a rumor that if you catch a Drifblim floating on the wind at dusk, you'll be carried away to the afterlife.
Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.
Its roar in battle shakes the ground like a tremor–or like an earthquake has struck.
A kindly Pokémon that lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.
Its electric-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.
What gives meaning to its life is surprising others. If you set your ear against the red orbs around its neck, you can hear shrieking.
It uses its claws to poke holes in eggs so it can slurp out the insides. Breeders consider it a scourge and will drive it away or eradicate it.
Its lithe muscles allow it to walk without making a sound. It attacks in an instant.
It makes a conical pit in desert sand and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.
It searches for food all day. It gnaws on hard objects to wear down its fangs, which grow constantly during its lifetime.
Once it has whipped up a sandstorm to halt its opponents in their tracks, this terrifying Pokémon snatches away their vitality.
It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.
Blades comprise this Pokémon's entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.
It captivates foes with its huge, round eyes, then lulls them to sleep by singing a soothing melody.
By spinning its body, it can dig straight through the ground at a speed of 30 mph.
Its cells are all magnets. It uses magnetism to communicate with others of its kind.
It lived in the same environments as Rampardos. Their fossils have been found together—seemingly from after they'd fought to the finish.
A Pokémon with persistent nature, it chases its prey until the prey becomes exhausted.
The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.
They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.
Its large eyes can scan 360 degrees. It looks in all directions to seek out insects as its prey.
Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.
Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to sleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing, it drains their vitality with its fingertips.
Normally friendly, it quickly becomes angry if it doesn't get what it wants.
Very protective of its territory, it flaps its short wings busily to dart around at high speed.
Using the long fur on its arms like whips, it launches into combo attacks that, once started, no one can stop.
Its cute act is a ruse. When victims let down their guard, they find their items taken. It attacks with sharp claws.
It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.
Instead of hands, it uses its tongue, which is twice its height. Its sticky saliva grips anything.
It is believed that the variety of types of this Pokémon were created by evolutionary adaptation, as each possesses a different ability.
It converses with others by using magnetic pulses. In a swarm, they move in perfect unison.
It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.
These key collectors threaten any attackers by fiercely jingling their keys at them.
It has a sad history. In the past, its dorsal fin was a treasured foodstuff, so this Pokémon became a victim of overfishing.
Now armed with a weapon it used in ancient times, this Pokémon needs only a single strike to fell even Gigantamax Pokémon.
When it spots enemies, it threatens them by jingling the scales on its tail. Weak opponents will crack and flee in panic.
Extremely cautious, they take shifts to maintain a constant watch of their nest. They feel insecure without a lookout.
It lives in treetop colonies. If one becomes enraged, the whole colony rampages for no reason.
It loves eating mushrooms that grow under dead grass. It also finds hot springs while foraging.
When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.
It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.
A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.
It attacks using its huge mouth. While its attacks are powerful, it hurts itself out of clumsiness, too.
This Pokémon lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.
It is believed that the variety of types of this Pokémon were created by evolutionary adaptation, as each possesses a different ability.
With its huge and magnificent wings, it can keep aloft without ever having to land or rest.
Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures' emotions. If you don't have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.
It leads a group of Pawniard. It battles to become the boss, but will be driven from the group if it loses.
A kindly Pokémon that lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.
It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.
Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.
Although small, its venomous barbs make this Pokémon dangerous. The female has smaller horns.
It drowses and dreams all the time. It's best to leave it be if it's just woken up, as it's a terrible grump when freshly roused from sleep.
Their cute act is a ruse. They trick people and steal their valuables just to see the looks on their faces.
Its milk is high in calories and packed with nutrients. Therefore, if you drink too much of it, you may wind up with a body like Miltank's.
A dangerous Ultra Beast, it appears to be eating constantly, but for some reason its droppings have never been found.
If it rampages, it knocks down mountains and buries rivers. Maps must be redrawn afterward.
It can return to its Trainer's location regardless of the distance separating them.
To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.
It is shrouded by blue vines. No one has seen the face hidden behind this growth of vines.
Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.
When two Beldum link together, their psychic power is doubled. Their intelligence, however, remains unchanged.
It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.
